    accordion.item([attribute.open(True)], [
      accordion.trigger([], [
        icon.user([]),
        html.h3([], [html.text("Account")]),
      ]),
      accordion.content([], [
        html.p([attribute.class("text-muted-foreground")], [
          html.text(
            "Update your name, email, and the avatar shown next to your
            comments.",
          ),
        ]),
      ]),
    ]),
    accordion.item([], [
      accordion.trigger([], [
        icon.shield([]),
        html.h3([], [html.text("Security")]),
      ]),
      accordion.content([], [
        html.p([attribute.class("text-muted-foreground")], [
          html.text(
            "Turn on two-factor authentication and review the devices signed
            in to your account.",
          ),
        ]),
      ]),
    ]),
    accordion.item([], [
      accordion.trigger([], [
        icon.layout_template([]),
        html.h3([], [html.text("Workspace")]),
      ]),
      accordion.content([], [
        html.p([attribute.class("text-muted-foreground")], [
          html.text(
            "Rename the workspace, set its default landing page, and manage
            shared templates.",
          ),
        ]),
      ]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

## API Reference

### Variants

Sets the accordion's visual style. Pass one into the root's attribute list.

| Variant | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `accordion.ghost()` | The default borderless stack with hairline separators between rows. |
| `accordion.outline()` | Bordered rows collapsed into a single outlined group, no fill. |
| `accordion.filled()` | Bordered, filled rows collapsed into a single group. |

### Elements

The root container and the composition elements that nest inside it.

| Element | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `accordion.root(attrs, children)` | The root container. Holds the items and carries the variant attribute. |
| `accordion.item(attrs, children)` | A single collapsible row. |
| `accordion.trigger(attrs, children)` | Clickable row header. Toggles its parent item open or closed. |
| `accordion.content(attrs, children)` | Body of a row, revealed when its parent item is open. |

### Attributes

Standard Lustre attributes an accordion item responds to. Pass them through the attribute list.

| Attribute | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `attribute.open(True)` | Defaults the item to its expanded state. |
| `attribute.name("faq")` | Groups items into an exclusive set; opening one closes the others. |
| `attribute.inert(True)` | Disables all interaction with the row and mutes it visually. |

### Selectors

CSS selectors stamped on the accordion's markup, available for overriding or layering app-specific styles.

| Selector | Matches |
| --- | --- |
| `[data-slot="accordion"]` | The root container. |
| `[data-variant="ghost\|outline\|filled"]` | The root, tagged with its active variant. |
| `[data-slot="accordion-item"]` | Each row (the details element). |
| `[data-slot="accordion-item"][open]` | An expanded row. |
| `[data-slot="accordion-item"][inert]` | A muted, non-interactive row. |
| `[data-slot="accordion-trigger"]` | The clickable row header (the summary element). |
| `[data-slot="accordion-trigger-icon"]` | The chevron appended to the end of every trigger. |
| `[data-slot="accordion-content"]` | The body revealed when its row is open. |

## Accessibility

**Keyboard & screen reader ready.** Each item renders as a native `<details>`/`<summary>` pair, so expanding, collapsing, and exclusive name grouping come from the browser rather than from script, and each trigger's expanded state is announced through the same built-in semantics. Inert items drop out of both the tab order and the accessibility tree.

### Keyboard

| Key | Action |
| --- | --- |
| Tab | Move focus to the next trigger (and any focusable content inside an open panel). |
| Shift + Tab | Move focus to the previous trigger (and any focusable content inside an open panel). |
| Enter | Toggle the focused item open or closed. |
| Space | Toggle the focused item open or closed. |

